						               													<description>Become Earth's protector or destroy humanity? The choice is yours in Risiko Transformers: Die Invasion der Decepticons, which puts players on the side of the Decepticons, who are invading Earth, or Optimus Prime and his Autobots, who are protecting the human race!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game starts with an inhabited human world with the Autobots in the center of the game board. The Decepticons invade from the four corners of the world, and as the game progresses they can take human slaves to repair and rebuild damaged units! Humans and Autobots always work together, but Decepticons can choose to ally with one another or fight amongst themselves. The survival of all depends on the Transformers' Energon &amp;mdash; and once the stock is used up, the game is over!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The objective of the game differs depending on whether you play the Decepticons or Autobots. The aim of the Decepticons is to conquer the Earth and enslave humanity. The more human slaves and territories controlled by the Decepticons, the more units they can send. The aim of the Autobots is to defend the Earth and ensure the survival of humanity. The more territories they recapture from the Decepticons, the more units they can send.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Risiko Transformers: Die Invasion der Decepticons is being released on the 30th anniversary of the Transformers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
